g.text: Title: TANDY WP-2 256K ROM IC Card
Manual says NC, but connects to IC5 pin 68
If the NC pins (15, 16, 36) were really NC inside the WP-2, then it would be possible to eliminate the write-enable JP1
by connecting R~W~ to ~WE~ through pins 15 & 16, and have the programming adapter short 15 to 16 with a trace.
But 15, 16, & 36 all actually have traces going to RA5 and IC5. IC5 is a gate-array with unknown programming.
It may not be safe to drive R~W~ into one of the IC5 pins.
It may not be safe to let ~WE~ be driven by one of the IC5 pins.
That is why those pins are left untouched even though they are nominally NC and available.
Card Detect: GND for RAM, NC for ROM
Manual says NC, but connects to IC5 pin 66
CE2 doesn't actually switch. It's shorted to VDD inside the WP-2.
Manual says NC, but connects to IC5 pin 67
